:"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: habitational name from any of various places, notably the barony of Drummond, which is probably identical with the parish of Drymen (Stirlingshire), named from Gaelic <i>drumainn</i>, a derivative of <i>druim</i> ‘ridge’. It has been said that the principal family of this name are descended from a Hungarian nobleman, Maurice, who accompanied Edgar Atheling and his sister Margaret to Scotland in 1068, where she married King Malcolm III. However, there is disagreement on whether or not this was the case.","English: occasionally perhaps from an unrecorded Middle English personal name <i>Dromund</i> (Old Norse <i>Drómundr</i>, apparently from a word denoting a kind of Byzantine galley prevalent till the 12th cent., from Greek <i>dromōn</i> ‘runner’)."],"variants":[{"name":"Drummonds","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Drummond  , with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>. In Britain this surname is found mainly in County Durham."]}]},{"name":"Sir","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Old Norse, originally a byname meaning ‘bride, wife’; in mythology the name of Thor's golden-haired wife."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Malcolm","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Anglicized form of the medieval Gaelic name <i>Mael Coluim</i> ‘devotee of St Columba’. Columba was a 6th-century monk of Irish origin who played a leading part in the conversion to Christianity of Scotland and northern England;  see also  Callum   and   Colm .  He has always been one of the most popular saints in Scotland, but in the Middle Ages it was felt to be presumptuous to give the names of saints directly to children; instead their blessing was invoked by prefixing the name with <i>mael</i> ‘devotee of’ or <i>gille</i> ‘servant of’. Since the 1930s the given name has been used widely in the English-speaking world, not just by those with Scottish connections."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Malcolm Drummond 5th Thane of Lennox was born about 1165, in Drymen, Stirlingshire, Scotland, United Kingdom, his father, John Drummond 4th Thane of Lennox, was 32 and his mother, Mrs Drummond, was 27. He married Margaret Lindsay before 1190, in Scotland. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died in 1200, in Stirling, Aberdeenshire, Scotland, at the age of 36, and was buried in Scotland."},"et":{"about 1165–1200":"umbes 1165–1200","1160–1200":"1160–1200","1165–1200":"1165–1200","1160–1240":"1160–1240","1190–1259":"1190–1259","1195–1283":"1195–1283","1135–1180":"1135–1180","1140–Female":"1140–Surnud","1190":"1190","about 1195":"umbes 1195","1165":"1165","from 1180 to 1200":"1180 kuni 1200","1240":"1240","1140":"1140","1283":"1283","1195":"1195","1160":"1160","1180":"1180","1259":"1259","1135":"1135","1200":"1200","about 1165":"umbes 1165","before 1190":"enne 1190","Drymen, Stirlingshire, Scotland":"Drymen, Stirlingshire, Scotland","Stirling, Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Stirling, Aberdeenshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fi":{"about 1165–1200":"noin 1165–1200","1160–1200":"1160–1200","1165–1200":"1165–1200","1160–1240":"1160–1240","1190–1259":"1190–1259","1195–1283":"1195–1283","1135–1180":"1135–1180","1140–Female":"1140–Kuollut","1190":"1190","about 1195":"noin 1195","1165":"1165","from 1180 to 1200":"vuodesta 1180 vuoteen 1200","1240":"1240","1140":"1140","1283":"1283","1195":"1195","1160":"1160","1180":"1180","1259":"1259","1135":"1135","1200":"1200","about 1165":"noin 1165","before 1190":"ennen vuotta 1190","Drymen, Stirlingshire, Scotland":"Drymen, Stirlingshire, Scotland","Stirling, Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Stirling, Aberdeenshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fr":{"about 1165–1200":"environ 1165–1200","1160–1200":"1160–1200","1165–1200":"1165–1200","1160–1240":"1160–1240","1190–1259":"1190–1